<div class="row_picture_inner_txt">
<h1>Facts checking: Latency and skyDSL</h1>
There are two important factors regarding data transfer to taking into account: The delay from input into a system to desired outcome (Latency) and the speed of data transfer. A perfect Internet connection would have then, no latency and an infinite Bandwidth. But in reality all Internet connections have their Bandwidth limitations and latency.<br/><br/>However, the latency plays a role only with slow Internet connections and very small amount of data. Even with less than 0,25 MB the skyDSL can deliver a faster&nbsp; Internet connection than the conventional slow DSL connection. This is less than a small website.<br/><br/>skyDSL thus, accomplishes not only the technological masterpiece data quality to be transmitted securely up to four times around the earth in a fraction of second, but it is comparable to the most fast DSL connections available despite of its latency. Useful delighted technology!
<h2>Online gaming with skyDSL</h2>
Most online games have no special requirements regarding latency. Especially web-based online games work with skyDSL significantly better than with conventional slow Internet connections. An exception is the group of so-called Ego-shooter. Here, the combination of a normal DSL connection and skyDSL can be useful. So you have low latencies and high bandwidths and thus the best of both worlds.
